message.content:
A cougar is a large predatory cat native to the Americas. 
It has a tan to reddish-brown fur that has a sleek and shiny texture. 
The cougar has a muscular and agile body with a long tail. 
It has round ears with black tips and a distinctive short snout and jawline. 
Cougars are typically found in mountainous regions and forest habitats. 
They are solitary and have a keen sense of hearing and vision. 
In popular culture, the term 'cougar' is also used to describe an older woman who is interested in dating younger men.
